<doc f='llvm/clang/include/clang/Parse/Parser.h' l='2338'>// &quot;Tentative parsing&quot; functions, used for disambiguation. If a parsing error
  // is encountered they will return TPResult::Error.
  // Returning TPResult::True/False indicates that the ambiguity was
  // resolved and tentative parsing may stop. TPResult::Ambiguous indicates
  // that more tentative parsing is necessary for disambiguation.
  // They all consume tokens, so backtracking should be used after calling them.</doc>
